Now let me implement the contour integral approach. The idea: instead of computing individual zeta zeros and summing x^ρ/ρ, evaluate the sum as a contour integral of (ζ'/ζ)(s) · x^s/s. If ζ'/ζ can be evaluated at fewer points than there are zeros (via some quadrature trick), we win.
