    6	## Motivation
    7	
    8	The explicit formula pi(x) = li(x) - sum_rho li(x^rho) + ... looks like a trace:
    9	Tr(f(A)) where A has eigenvalues {rho}. In random matrix theory, Tr(f(A)) can
    10	sometimes be computed from matrix entries via moments Tr(A^k), avoiding eigenvalue
    11	enumeration. Can this shortcut work for zeta zeros?
    12	
    13	## Experiment 1 & 5: Moments Method
